messages.message: I’ve a demo to Citi on Fri
can you use precomputed results for your Citi demo?
with Aaron in Singapore, I'm not sure we'll be able to debug this before then.
Maybe if everyone stopped using adverse news for the next 2 days, we can see if the rate limit issue goes away?

@Anant ok digging into it some more, I don't think we can do anything active about this until next week.

Our options are:
we can stop using adverse news search and pray it works again in the next day or two, *or*
we can drop everything (SC, other goals for this release) and have Aaron work solely on this for the next 3 days.
so that is higher priority than anything else
I think Aaron made a quick fix
I think the quick fix was to wait for google to stop rate limiting us
or you mean when there was a dom change? if we need him to debug that, that'll pull a lot of time away from SC

I would love to be able to do a quick fix here, but our technical debt is piled so high we don't even know where the issue is. i.e. logs give us super poor visibility into where in the pipeline the error is happening, so just figuring that out will take several hours

I can almost guarantee there is no dom change because a lot of other sites and tools rely on google search scraping, I think we would hear about it. This is the exact behavior we have seen before 4-5 times and waiting it out is usually the best fix
That quick fix was neither of those things, that fix I mentioned shaunak about is a different thing regarding NLP Pipelines (with NLP Search does not use yet)

I’m about to pass out from jetlag but I would recommend letting NLP Search cool down for a few hours and then trying again. Tomorrow, depending on my prep for the JPMC workshop + SC use cases, I can try to look into this a tiny bit
yea get some rest - we'll handle it!
